{
  "texts": [
    "Each greyscale image was 64 × 228 pixels (with values between 0 and 255) depicting a fictive female fly on a white background (see 'Visual input reconstruction').",
    "Before being fed into the network, the input was first re-centred by subtracting 255 from each pixel intensity to ensure the background pixels had values of 0.",
    "The model's output was six behavioural variables of the male fly: forward velocity, lateral velocity, angular velocity, probability of sine song, probability of Pfast song, and probability of Pslow song (see 'Courtship experiments').",
    "Vision network.",
    "The first layer of the vision network was spatial convolutions with 32 filters (kernel size 3 × 3) and a downsampling stride of 2."
  ]
}